    "title": {
      "rendered": "ATTN Nonprofits: Facebook Now Recommends Pages in the News Feed"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/facebook-recommendations.jpg\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-14401\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"facebook-recommendations\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/facebook-recommendations-300x300.jpg?resize=300%2C300\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/facebook-recommendations.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/facebook-recommendations.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/facebook-recommendations.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/facebook-recommendations.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/facebook-recommendations.jpg?w=500&amp;ssl=1 500w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a>Facebook now also recommends pages in the news feed, but only if your nonprofit has opted-in to have your page recommended. Until today page recommendations only occurred when individuals liked a page, but now recommendations are also given when individuals like a status update in the news feed. Facebook has not officially announced the new functionality, so it may only be a temporary upgrade and not for all users, but for however long the functionality exists ensuring that your page is optimized for recommendations is a simple way to gain new fans.</p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Facebook Admin Panel &gt; Settings &gt; Similar Page Suggestions</strong></h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/settings.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-14395\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"settings\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/settings.png?resize=600%2C285\" width=\"600\" height=\"285\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/settings.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/settings.png?resize=300%2C142&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Page Recommendations in the News Feed<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/graspunep\">facebook.com/graspunep</a><br />\n</strong></h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/gorilla.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-14396\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"gorilla\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/gorilla.png?resize=496%2C583\" width=\"496\" height=\"583\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/gorilla.png?w=496&amp;ssl=1 496w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/gorilla.png?resize=255%2C300&amp;ssl=1 255w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 496px) 100vw, 496px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Page Recommendations on Pages<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/whales.org\">facebook.com/whales.org</a></strong></h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/whales.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-14398\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"whales\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/whales.png?resize=600%2C400\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/whales.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/whales.png?resize=300%2C200&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n",
      "protected": false
    },
    "excerpt": {
      "rendered": "<p>Facebook now also recommends pages in the news feed, but only if your nonprofit has opted-in to have your page recommended. Until today page recommendations only occurred when individuals liked a page, but now recommendations are also given when individuals like a status update in the news feed. Facebook has not officially announced the new functionality, so it may only be a temporary upgrade and not for all users, but for however long the functionality exists ensuring that your page is optimized for recommendations is a simple way to gain new fans. Facebook Admin Panel &gt; Settings &gt; Similar Page </p>\n",
